Van rises from the chair, eyeglasses flashing, and pours the nearest wine into each of their wineglasses. The room is warmed by a dusty gas heater from the Fifties. In the centre of the table sits a squat wax candle in a saucer, burning a dark, a dusky yellow. James checks the time in the midst of the voices around him, comments he misses, waves of laughter. Two in the morning. He looks up at Evelyn. She?s talking to the housemates.